It’s understood the residents are protesting over power cuts. JOHANNESBURG - Police have confirmed a group of almost 100 people have staged a protest in Katlehong blocking off Thutong Street leading up to the Chris Hani Mall. It’s understood the residents are protesting over power cuts. Ekurhuleni metro police spokesperson Wilfred Kgasakgo said, “We will meet them on Wednesday and they are prepared to disperse now.”